reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful base and organizing for our daughters art table
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the 5-Drawer Chest, Wood Storage Dresser Cabinet with Wheels in White, and it has exceeded my expectations in terms of both style and functionality.Firstly, the design is sleek and modern, adding a touch of elegance to my bedroom. The crisp white finish complements my decor seamlessly, creating a clean and organized look. The compact size is perfect for smaller spaces, and the addition of wheels makes it incredibly convenient to move around and rearrange as needed.Assembly was fine, it took a few hours, and the drawers slide effortlessly. The five drawers offer ample storage space for clothes, accessories, or any other items you need to keep tidy. I appreciate the varying drawer sizes, providing versatility for organizing different items.The build quality is impressive, with sturdy wood construction ensuring durability. The drawer handles are both functional and stylish, adding a nice finishing touch to the overall design.What sets this dresser apart is its versatility. Whether you need extra storage in your bedroom, guest room, or even in a living space, this dresser fits the bill.In conclusion, the 5-Drawer Chest, Wood Storage Dresser Cabinet with Wheels in White is a fantastic addition to any home. It combines style, functionality, and convenience in one package. If you're in need of a practical and aesthetically pleasing storage solution, look no further. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I purchased the 7 drawer in Black for my office. It took 5 hours to put together. That is my only complaint. It looks great, good quality, and enough room in each drawer for office supplies. I have to laugh at one ridiculous photo I saw with drill holes all over the boards. Everything is predrilled. No drill needed! Pay not attention to that photo. The 7 drawer WILL hold scrap book paper with room to spare. Inside drawer approx. 13" x 15 1/4" give or take. I believe the 9 drawer has smaller drawers and does not fit the scrap book paper.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars While assembly isn't trivial, it comes together for a nice, functional, piece.
reviews.reviewText: I actually enjoyed assembling this piece. The parts fit well together, all drilled holes align well, and cuts seem pretty square. Once fully assembled, the drawers are centered and glide easily, gaps are small and even, and unit is very sturdy. My only complaint is that two of the drawer faces had noticeable nicks on their edges. I was able to touch them up, but I would have liked all unblemished drawer faces. I also wish the manufacture would substitute something more environmentally friendly than styrofoam for packing.This piece has the most parts of any piece of DIY furniture I've assembled (258+ and I didn't use the 20 for the castor wheels), but, once completed, it is nice looking piece that perfectly suited my needs. It took me about 3 hours to complete, but I take some steps other may not take. First, I lay everything out in assembly-line fashion, making sure I have all the parts. Second (and I recommend this step to everyone), I used wood glue on all the wooden dowel pins. The cam lock connectors used in this piece (and in most DIY furniture) are pretty cheap, especially when used with particle board. They either bottom out too easily or they won't stay tight over time. Either way, their use generally results in loose and unstable joints. However, they do make decent 'clamps' for holding the panels in place while the wood glue dries. Wood glue is far superior to the cams and extends the usefulness of the furniture by years (I have Sauder bookcases I built 24 years ago that are still solid - even after multiple moves). I recommend Titebond II wood glue, but even Elmers would be better than just the cams alone. Finally, I don't skip steps.The instructions are fairly clear, and anyone who's ever done DIY furniture before shouldn't have any issues. Several points, though. You might be tempted, as I was, to secure the drawer bottoms with small nails (not included). Initially, it seems as though they will not be secured and will sag. But, once the drawer slide rails are added to the drawers, the bottoms are secured. Second, you might be tempted to skip attaching the plastic inserts against the back panels in the final step. Don't. It's not intuitive that these 8 small plastic pieces would do much of anything, but they actually add detectable stability to the unit. Finally, and I can't stress this enough: do not over-tighten cam pins or screws. Particle board is a poor material, but it will work for light furniture until you strip it over-tightening a screw. Wood glue can be used to repair the hole (put glue in stripped hole, insert screw, let dry completely), but the repair will be weaker than an unstripped hole, which isn't that great to start with.To summarize, not a bad piece of DIY furniture. With a little care and patience, following the instructions, the chest should provide years of function and decent aesthetics for a reasonable price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This set of drawers is fantastic. I got it to replace the janky plastic drawers I had forever. This provides more storage place and is sturdy for my printer. I measured before buying and it is a perfect fit for the little nook I needed it for. It’s sturdy, the drawers slide smoothly and pull out almost the whole way so you can truly take advantage of all the storage it offers. This is definitely an office supply or makeup product type storage, the drawers aren’t very deep but perfect for the above things. It took about 3 hours to put together and it was a bit of a pain but that’s because it was stop-and-go since I was working while putting it together. The directions are clear and correct, follow them! For the drawers I bought the Criusia 25 pack drawer organizer (also here on Amazon) and they’ve filled up almost 4 drawers mixing and matching the pieces. Love it overall!

Je suis ravie de cette commande. J'ai acheté 2 tours. Elles ont été très simples à monter, si tous les meubles pouvaient être aussi simples, ce serait bien! Toutes les pièces sont numérotées. Les trous sont bien faits, aux bons endroits.Ils sont très bien pensés. Les fonds de tiroirs et fond du meuble très bien maintenus.Les tiroirs coulissent parfaitement, se placent bien parallèles dans le meuble.J'ai passé cette commande le 31 Mai, livraison prévue entre le 1er juillet et le 4, je l'ai reçue le 5 juin!Je n'ai qu'un point négatif à soulever, une des planches d'un tiroir était abîmée, voir la photo. Mais cela n'a pas gêné au montage du meuble et n'a pas fragilisé la tenue du fond du tiroir et ça ne se voit absolument pas. J'avais enlevé une étoile au début pour ce défaut mais à la réflexion, le meuble n'en est pas affecté, donc je lui laisse 5*.Oh et un autre mini point négatif, il y a un autocollant sur le dessus du meuble et quand on l'enlève il laisse des traces de colle mais avec de l'acétone végétale, ça part sans abîmer la couleur du meuble.Je recommande vraiment l'achat de ses tours de tiroirs. Je partais avec un léger à priori car meubles en "compressé" mais franchement ils sont top. La simplicité du design fait qu'ils passent partout sans dénoter.

Montage hat gedauert, war aber gut erklärt - und das Produkt ist wirklich schön anzusehen und praktisch.Nur roch das Möbelstück eine Weile streng, und die Platten waren auch fleckig (fettig?) Nach Behandlung mit Möbelpolitur aber nun ein Schmuckstück.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 2, 2020
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to go in a kitchen cupboard to hold all my bits and pieces. Arrived well packaged but there was slight damage to the base, but as this was going into a cupboard it didn’t matter. Was worried when I saw the hardboard bases to the draws but they are held firmly in place with the the draw rails. Assembly instructions were easy to follow. All in all quite happy with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 3, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I ordered 2 sets of these Drawers. Everything was easy to assemble. 1 set of of drawers had missing caster wheels. I sent a message to Devaise's Facebook page regarding the missing caster wheels. I got asked to circle ⭕ the caster wheels & take a photo from the manual that came in the box. They asked for my Amazon order number & address. Within 7 days I received the caster wheels direct from the Chinese supplier with TNT tracking number (FedEx package) 😁👍

Wir haben das Modell (schwarz) wohl anscheinend gebraucht bekommen. Das verrieten die vielen Fingerabdrücke und Wischspuren, die wir auch nicht mehr entfernen konnten. (Ebenso waren die Tütchen geöffnet).Vielleicht war der Lack auch fehlerhaft, so eine Oberfläche sollte sich ja eigentlich reinigen lassen. Dafür war der Container immerhin gut 3 Wochen vorher da, als angekündigt. Der Zusammenbau war so lala,.... 2 1/2 Stunden rumgeschlagen.... wir haben vor 2 Jahren den (leider nicht mehr in schwarz erhältlichen) „Kollegen“ von dem schwedischen Möbelhaus gekauft, das war auf jeden Fall eine bessere Qualität.
